Running under a protected memory process i.e. the 'Amiga'
won't be able to crash Neutrino (QNX is a different product).
The Amiga will be able to access what it likes - because it
is in it's own little memory space, it thinks it has 64Mb
of RAM going, and Neutrino can't stop a process from writing
into memory that the process actually owns.

Neutrino is perfectly capable (and probably will) run straight
out of FlashROM with little or no memory overhead. A bit of
stack space, maybe?

But no more imposing than using PrepareEmul to shift your
memory space up by 4kb.

