Hi,

On Fri, 12 Nov 1999, Michael Schulze wrote:
> BTW: Is it possible to render to a window on the WB and still get HW-support?
> I don't managed it to run WarpTest in a window. Or is this just possible with
> the new release of Warp3D (WO2097 runs in a window...)?

There are different ways of rendering to a window. The first one is to
render in a bitmap that's allocated off-screen (via AllocBitMap), and blit
that to the window. This version is independant of the used screen
depth/resolution. 
The second possibility is to directly render into a window. But this is
only possible if the screen is of a format that's supported by the
appropriate chip. Otherwise, Warp3D will reject the drawing surface with
an 'illegal format' error.

Remember, you can use W3D_SetDrawRegion to supply Warp3D with a BitMap...

