> game down? How many polys are there on screen at the same time (approx)?

In high resolutions the fill rate of the Permedia2 slows down the
applications. The Permedia2 is already a very old chip when looking
at state-of-the-art chips on PC. Additionally the bus performance also limits
the game performance, especially for high polygon count.

There are several thousands of polygons on the screen at high view distance,
while the amount of polygons probably go down more than linearly with
the reduction of the view distance.
 
