The WarpUp archive on the 3.5 CD is the same archive as the WarpUp 4
archive which is found on H&P's FTP server, therefore it contains the older
ppc.library emulation. You should also know, that for projects like OS3.5
it is impossible to continously keep the pace with new releases of third
party products. Sure, a later version of ppclibemu could have been added
to the WarpUp archive, but how long would it be new enough? It would
probably take just a few weeks, until it is outdated again, and bringing
out OS updates is something very different to simply releasing new versions
of small freeware products.

Those people which always want to have the latest version of ppclibemu
should check Aminet regularly and get the latest versions through Internet.
OS releases are not suitable to get latest versions of such software.

Whenever a new WarpUp release will be done, the latest ppclibemu will
be added to the WarpUp archive. And finally, please note: ppclibemu is
neither developed nor maintained by H&P. It is a contribution to the WarpUp
archive, which is beeing developed by Frank Wille. It's entirely up to him to
decide about further development of the software, so if you have any questions
related to ppclibemu you should ask the questions to him.

